Add Custom Actions in Case Feed

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
User permission required: Customize Application

Actions in Case Feed let support agents perform tasks like emailing customers, writing case notes, and changing the status of a case. You can use Visualforce pages to create custom actions that offer agents more functionality.

To add custom actions:

From object management settings for cases, go to Page Layouts.
Click Edit, then click Feed View in the page layout editor.
Click + Add a Visualforce Page in the list of custom actions.
Select the page you want to add as an action.
Specify the height of the action in pixels.
Click Save.

You can use any Visualforce page that uses the standard case controller as a custom action.
title: Custom Actions in Service Cloud
